│ stop({"edit_points": [[7587, 7595,                                            │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp"]], "thoughts": "1.          │
│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe loop-vectorizer crashes on the provided IR due  │
│ to an assertion in                                                            │
│ LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF():\nassert((BestFactor.Width ==       │
│ LegacyVF.Width || PlanForEarlyExitLoop ||                                     │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width), CostCtx,  │
│ OrigLoop) ||                                                                  │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(LegacyVF.Width), CostCtx,    │
│ OrigLoop)) && \" VPlan cost model and legacy cost model disagreed\");\nThis   │
│ asserts that if the selected VF from the new VPlan cost model differs from    │
│ the legacy cost model's VF, the discrepancy must be explainable by early-exit │
│ structure or detectable \"additional simplifications\" (missing instructions  │
│ / partial reductions) in one of the plans.\nIn the reproducer, the VF choices │
│ differ, but none of the allowed escape conditions evaluate to true, so the    │
│ assertion fires.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nScalarEvolution shows a constant │
│ trip count (100) and no reductions. The loop body contains operations that    │
│ become trivially invariant or foldable (e.g. shl; ashr exact; select with an  │
│ invariant input). The VPlan cost model likely folds or treats some invariant  │
│ operations (and potentially UB-inducing remainder with a zero divisor) as     │
│ free or merged, reducing vector cost. The legacy cost model still accounts    │
│ for each original instruction individually because                            │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications only flags instructions totally missing │
│ from the plan, or partial reduction recipes. Thus a legitimate cost-model     │
│ divergence arises but is not classified as an \"additional                    │
│ simplification\".\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe root cause is that          │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications is too narrow: it only detects cases    │
│ where instructions are entirely absent (no recipe) or partial reductions. It  │
│ does not recognize intra-recipe simplifications (e.g. combining shl+ashr,     │
